Task Tracker CLI

A simple Command Line Interface (CLI) Task Tracker built using Node.js.
It helps you manage tasks directly from the terminal with features like adding, updating, deleting, and tracking task status.

🚀 Features
Add new tasks
Update task description
Delete tasks
Mark tasks as:
Todo by default
In Progress
Done
List all tasks
Filter tasks by status
Stores data in a local JSON file
Colored terminal output (Git-like UI)
🛠️ Tech Stack
Node.js
File System (fs module)
JSON storage
Chalk (for colored output)
📂 Project Structure
TaskTracker/
│── app.js
│── tasks.json
│── package.json
⚙️ Installation

Clone the project:
git clone "https://github.com/Himanshu-0076/Backend-Learning/tree/main/TaskTracker"
Move into project folder:
cd TaskTracker
Install dependencies:
npm install
Install chalk (important):
npm install chalk@4
▶️ How to Run

Run commands using Node.js:

➕ Add Task
node app.js add "Learn JavaScript"
📋 List All Tasks
node app.js list
🔍 Filter Tasks
node app.js list done
node app.js list todo
node app.js list in-progress
✏️ Update Task
node app.js update 1 "Learn Node.js"
❌ Delete Task
node app.js delete 1
🚧 Mark Task as In Progress
node app.js mark-in-progress 1
✅ Mark Task as Done
node app.js mark-done 1
📦 Data Storage

All tasks are stored in:

tasks.json

Example format:

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "description": "Learn Node.js",
    "status": "todo"
  }
]
🎨 Output Example
Id: 1 | Learn JS | todo
Id: 2 | Build API | done
Id: 3 | Practice | in-progress
💡 Key Concepts Used
process.argv (CLI arguments)
File System (fs module)
JSON parsing & stringifying
Array methods (map, filter, forEach)
Conditional logic
Ternary operator
Error handling (try/catch)
🧠 Learning Outcome

This project helps you understand:

How CLI tools work
Backend logic without database
File-based data storage
Real-world CRUD operations
JavaScript array manipulation
